Perform predictions on new data

Source: R/predict_new.R
predict_new.Rd

This function is used when the user created the models and evaluated them on a datset x and later on, he got new observations and wants to predict the target value for them. The `predict_new()` function quickly normalizes their format, like a subset of columns that were deleted for the models and makes predictions. It is strongly advised that the new dataset shouldn't have any missing values.

predict_new(train_out, data, verbose = TRUE)

Arguments

train_out

The output of the `train()` function.

data

A dataset with the same format as the one used in `train()` function, but with new observations.

verbose

A logical value, if set to TRUE, provides all information about the process, if FALSE gives none.

Value

A list of predictions.
